Specific Fixes
Fix 1 — HTTP timeout (antigravity_service.dart):

// Before:
final res = await http.post(Uri.parse(...), ...);

// After:
final res = await http.post(Uri.parse(...), ...).timeout(
  const Duration(seconds: 10),
  onTimeout: () => http.Response('{"timeout":true}', 408),
);
Fix 2 — API key startup validation (agent.py):

# At module startup, before LlmAgent creation:
if not GOOGLE_API_KEY:
    raise RuntimeError("[CRITICAL] GOOGLE_API_KEY not set — refusing to start")
Fix 3 — Robust JSON extraction (agent.py ~L659):

import re
match = re.search(r'```(?:json)?\s*(.*?)\s*```', response_text, re.DOTALL)
if match:
    clean = match.group(1)
else:
    clean = response_text.strip()
Fix 4 — Safe cast in _parseActions (antigravity_service.dart):

List<AdaptationAction> _parseActions(dynamic actionsJson) {
  if (actionsJson is! List) return [];
  return actionsJson
    .whereType<Map<String, dynamic>>()
    .map((a) => AdaptationAction.fromJson(a))
    .toList();
}
What Looks Good
A2A orchestration is correctly implemented — Therapy Director → Story Weaver delegation is real multi-agent, not simulated
Quota/429 handling is well-thought-out — 60s cooldown + FixedRuleEngine fallback is production-grade
Offline fallback on Flutter side is clean — _localFallback() returns sensible defaults
Cultural design (Urdu/Roman Urdu bilingual TTS, Pakistan-specific context) is authentic
Async/await throughout FastAPI is correct — no blocking I/O
QC gate on Story Weaver output via _validate_quest() is good defensive architecture
Baseline benchmark toggle for hackathon judging is clever
Verdict: Request Changes
Before Cloud Run deployment: fix items 1, 2, 3, 4 (critical). Before hackathon submission: fix 6, 7, 8 (crashes under edge cases). Items 9–13 are polish.

The architecture is sound — the multi-agent ADK design is genuinely well-structured for a hackathon project. The gaps are mostly defensive hardening, not architectural flaws.